The paper deals with the Permutation Constraint Satisfaction Problem (Permutation CSP), which is a combinatorial optimization problem. The problem has connections to various areas of computer science, including algorithms and complexity (cs.DS, cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses exact algorithms for the problem, which suggests that it is more likely to be classified under cs.DS and cs.CC. However, the problem's connections to other areas of computer science make it possible to be classified under cs.AI, cs.DM, and cs.LG as well.
